# Context window closeout

**Triggers:** `close out thread` · `closeout thread` · `close this thread` · `end thread` · `context closeout` · `wrap this chat` · `thread handoff`

When the user uses any trigger above, or the chat is too long/noisy to continue:

1. Read [`docs/SOP/CONTEXT_WINDOW_CLOSEOUT_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/CONTEXT_WINDOW_CLOSEOUT_V1.md).
2. Run **`context_window_closeout.cmd --record`** (implies **auto-ship**: gate → commit → push → open PR → `automerge` label). Do **not** ask permission to commit, push, open PR, or merge.
3. Triage anything **blocked** by auto-ship (mixed-plane, gate fail) into backlog/park via draft report only when needed.
4. **Charter / explore / neutral thread:** on mixed-plane or branch recovery — **park only** (draft report); do **not** stash/checkout/rebase in closeout — operator thread owns recovery per [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc).
5. Complete `<!-- AGENT_FILL -->` sections in draft only when narrative/triage needs capture.
6. End with a **one-line** operator summary — **never** narrate commits, PR numbers, merge steps, git commands, stash pop, or relay verdicts unless auto-ship **blocked** and recovery is required.

**Operator-facing tone:** "Thread closed — work shipped" or "Thread closed — one item parked (see draft)." Not a git play-by-play.

**Not** chapter closeout (`apply_control_closeout_v1`) unless a relay closeout slice is also in scope.

**Next thread:** user asks `what's next?` in an **operator thread** — agent runs adaptive burst per `ppe-operator-core.mdc` (preflight + `@ppe-director` when allowed). Charter threads: see [`THREAD_STARTERS_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/THREAD_STARTERS_V1.md). **`ppe_go.cmd --single`** for one-shot handoff. Context: `WHATS_NEXT.md` + `AGENT_CONTINUITY_BRIEF.md` (no @ required).
